<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-17239] Race in CompactionExecutorTest</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17239</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;CompactionExecutorTest has a race between the runnable/callable under test completing&lt;br/&gt;
and the &lt;tt&gt;afterExecute&lt;/tt&gt; method stashing it for the test.  Replace the wait/sleep loop&lt;br/&gt;
with a &lt;tt&gt;SimpleCondition&lt;/tt&gt; that is signaled once the test task throwable has been recorded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seems fairly hard to hit but has happened on CI.  It took about 2600 iterations on my MacBook to trigger, but you can artificially hit frequently by adding a sleep at the start of the afterExecute method.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
